oiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Wiz</a><span> solving secu=
rity challenges presented by the cloud &#8211;&#160; there will always be n=
ew challenges to solve with radically better software tools.</span></p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Other industries, though, are </span><strong>matter ind=
ustries</strong><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Think energy or agricul=
ture. These things are necessarily physical. Electricity requires electrons=
=2E Digital food doesn&#8217;t fill be=
llies.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55=
, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">For the pas=
t few decades, as software has eaten the world, entrepreneurs and incumbent=
s alike have attempted to fix these industries with software. They&#8217;ve=
 made them more efficient, perhaps, but they&#8217;ve only nibbled around t=
he edges. Giving a power plant a CRM only does so much.</p><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">The fact is, physical challenges require physical solutions, and humans h=
ave spent millennia developing physical solutions.&#160;</p><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;">Matter industry incumbents got where they are by using tools that were n=
ewly available at the time of their formation to solve old challenges in ne=
w ways. They were once Techno-Industrials.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(=
54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Boein=
g is a dominant airplane manufacturer today because its 707 used a jet engi=
ne to cut travel times in half way back in 1958.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color=
: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"=
>Exxon Mobil (the result of a merger between Standard Oil of New Jersey and=
 Standard Oil of New York) is still the largest American energy company tod=
ay because Standard vertically integrated around innovations in refining te=
chniques, pipeline networks, storage and distribution, and more way back in=
 the late 19th century.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>You can&#8217;t bu=
ild a larger airline manufacturer than Boeing or a larger energy company th=
an Exxon Mobil with software alone </span><em>or </em><span>by making sligh=
tly better jet engines or oil refineries.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color=
: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"=
><span>Century-old incumbents have remained comfortably atop these industri=
es because attempts to innovate with software have been </span><strong>sust=
aining innovations</strong><span>. Incumbents have adopted the good ones to=
 improve their bottom lines, but software alone hasn&#8217;t </span><em>res=
haped</em><span> these industries.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(5=
4, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">You ne=
ed to introduce an entirely new paradigm, which requires reaching much high=
er on the cumulative technology ladder than previous solutions. Because whi=
le the accumulation of tools is continuous, there are discrete periods in h=
istory when those tools have gotten better enough to make new solutions pos=
sible.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I think we&#8217;re in one of those perio=
ds.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-heig=
ht: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Instead of designing slightly better v=
ersions of old products &#8211; not better </span><em>enough</em><span> to =
displace incumbents &#8211; or fixing inefficiencies with software, entrepr=
eneurs are designing radically better </span><strong>vertically integrated =
systems</strong><span> from the ground up with cutting edge hardware and so=
ftware.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">They&#8217;re mixing and matching=
 whatever tools are needed to get the job done: SaaS, AI, AR, mobile, crypt=
o, biotech, and all of the million things that go into what people call &#8=
220;deep tech.&#8221;</p><h3 class=3D"header-with-anchor-widget" style=3D"-=
