lative;"><strong>Anduril and Power Laws</strong></h3><p style=3D"color: rgb=
(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><spa=
n>When Anduril launched in 2017, it was famously met with a ton of skeptici=
sm. Some of it came from the fact that investors found defense distasteful,=
 but a lot of it came from a </span><strong>lack of knowledge about the def=
ense industry.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55=
, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Competing w=
ith the five Defense Primes? Yuck. Hardware? Yuck. Selling to the governmen=
t? Yuck.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">What Anduril&#8217;s founding team unde=
rstood, though, was that the tools had gotten good enough to build a defens=
e company with a fundamentally different approach.&#160;</p><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;">Advances in AI and software more broadly meant that it was possible to b=
uild Lattice, an operating system that connects all of Anduril&#8217;s hard=
ware. SpaceX showed that it was possible to manufacture hardware and sell i=
t to the government more cheaply than incumbents could. Together, they pres=
ented the opportunity to build a defense company with better margins.&#160;=
</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Over the past seven years, Anduril both proved that i=
t was possible to build a big business in defense and educated the market o=
n how the defense industry works. If you ask a random VC what &#8220;cost-p=
lus&#8221; means today, most will actually know what you&#8217;re talking a=
bout!&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>As Anduril co-founder Trae Stephens =
wrote in </span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/2f351271-0a47-=
4ed1-9423-6245cda9ec0b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqO=
sa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: under=
line;">Venture Capital&#8217;s Space for Sheep</a></em><span>:</span></p><b=
lockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: 20px 0; padding:=
 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em><span>Today, Anduril is value=
d at more than $10 billion, and the hype has followed. In 2014, just $200 m=
illion in venture investment flowed into defense technology; last year, tha=
t figure </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/aff8e78b-01cd-4065=
-8a54-a941aa6467e7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-=
6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline=
;">topped $6 billion</a><span>. Investors see our success as proof the defe=
nse industry can generate serious returns, and now they&#8217;re hoping to =
get a piece of the next Anduril.</span></em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px =
0;">That, Trae believes, is the wrong lesson to take from Anduril. &#8220;I=
n all likelihood,&#8221; he writes, &#8220;another defense tech company ope=
rating at Anduril&#8217;s scale won&#8217;t come out of this hype cycle.&#8=
221;&#160;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>The right lesson to take from=
 Anduril is that it&#8217;s possible to build very big businesses by applyi=
ng a suite of cutting edge tools and processes to the right bottlenecks in =
large, seemingly impenetrable industries.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p=
 style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;">And thanks to the power law, there will be one really big w=
inner in each industry:</p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b=
4e9; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>=
Defense, like all technology sectors, is ruled by the power law: a single, =
prime mover will claim the vast majority of profits even after the sector h=
as reached maturity. The company that carves out a new investment category =
usually stays on top.</em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 5=
5); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>In other=
 words, </span><strong>catching the power law winners</strong><span> </span=
><em><strong>requires</strong></em><strong> looking in new sectors.</strong=
></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Uber, he points out, has a market cap three times as=
 large as the next ten ride-sharing companies combined.&#160;</p><div class=
